# Vibefolio — project conventions

A live UI/UX showcase. Each section is an experimental piece. Code quality matters as much as the visual.

## Stack

- React 19 + TypeScript 5.7 (strict)
- Vite 6 (target `es2022`)
- Tailwind v4 with `@theme` design tokens (in `src/index.css`)
- Three.js + `@react-three/fiber` + `@react-three/drei`
- GSAP 3 + ScrollTrigger
- Lenis for smooth scroll (NOT used when `prefers-reduced-motion`)

## Folder layout

- `src/components/` — one file per section (NavBar, Hero, ProjectGrid, Methodology, Footer)
- `src/components/methodology/` — large shader/data assets that belong to a single section
- `src/lib/` — cross-section primitives (`useMotion`, `MotionProvider`, `easings`, `lazyR3F`)

When a component grows past ~400 LOC and contains shaders or data, split assets into a sibling folder named after the section.

## Design tokens

- Brand spectrum: `--color-cyan-deep` / `--color-cyan-pure` / `--color-cyan-glow` / `--color-violet-edge` / `--color-magenta-hot`
- MD3 aliases (`--color-primary-fixed`, `--color-on-surface-variant`, …) are still wired for retro-compat — prefer brand tokens for NEW code.
- Fluid display sizes: `--text-display-xl`, `--text-display-l`, `--text-display-m`, `--text-display-s`
- Easings (CSS): `--ease-glide`, `--ease-spring`, `--ease-snap`, `--ease-out-expo`
- Z-index scale: `--z-bg-shader`, `--z-content`, `--z-overlay`, `--z-nav`, `--z-cursor`, `--z-modal`

## Accessibility / quality tiers

`prefers-reduced-motion` and the `qualityTier` ("low" | "medium" | "high") are non-negotiable. See `vibefolio-motion.mdc`.

## What we DO NOT do

- No new fonts beyond Inter + JetBrains Mono.
- No `position: fixed` z-index races — always use the named scale.
- No leftover `Backup_*.tsx`, `dist/`, or duplicated scaffolds in the repo.
- No code comments that paraphrase the line below them (see global rules).
